                <note rend="inline" type="source">123C8812/15a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-28T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 28, 1923—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Your No. 58 of July 26, 1 p.m.,<note n="14" xml:id="d673fn14">Not
                        printed.</note> and your telephone conversation with Captain Rock. Also your
                    despatch No. 218, of July 24.<note n="14" xml:id="d673fn16">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Department desires that you should come to Washington for a conference as
                    soon as you deem it advisable.<note n="15" xml:id="d673fn15">The Ambassador left
                        Habana Aug. 2 and remained in the United States until Dec. 14.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
